19: The star of the show has arrived!
24: Sorry to keep you waiting, guys!
27:
Good timing. I was getting bored of
keeping the pumpkin-head
company. You got this?
31:
Leave the rest to us!
Falsche, let's go!
36:
Right... Jack-o'-Lantern, please show
us. How you feel.
38:
I'll be by your side. If you're lonely.
And so will Dia.
41:
Establishing supersized acoustic
space! Setting channel to maximum
levels of imagination!
45:
When Diva Media's on the air, all
souls and spirits stop and stare!
48:
All right, spirits of Palpebra, get
ready for a special Halloween
concert—a requiem, just for you!
60:
It must have been tough. For all you
sprites caught up in this.
63:
Jack-o'-Lantern... You should play
with them. More nicely next time.
Okay?
70:
Welcome back! I'm so glad to see
none of you are hurt.
72:
I don't know how I can ever repay
you for saving Kerry and Tonio!
75:
We were happy to help. By the way,
how did things go over here?
79:
Very well. Your song resonated
throughout the entire town.
83:
I'll have the Guild take care of the
rest, and send you your reward later
this week!
87:
Were all the ghosts we played with
today... real ghosts?
97:
But they weren't trying. To do
anything bad.
99:
They just wanted to. Enjoy the
festival. With everyone.
104:
We, um... We had a lot of fun with
them.
109:
That's good. 
I'm sure they had. Fun too.
114: I'm sorry. I was mean to you.
116:
You brought my dad's knife back...
So thank you!
119:
O-oh... Thank you. For taking care of
it.
122: Ehehe... That's all I wanted to say!
126:
It's nice he came around, isn't it?
Good for you, Falsche.
143: Trick or treat! Give us candy, or else!
151:
What do we do? I don't have any
candy...
155:
Sorry, I can't help this time. All my
treats got crushed when we were
fighting.
169:
Ahaha, it wouldn't be Halloween
without a few pranks, right?
173:
...Well, if this isn't the perfect chance
for some of my OWN mischief!
179:
D-don't cause them too much grief,
okay?
183:
*snicker* That sounds like
permission to me!
189:
Wh-wha... Renoir?! Taking
advantage of this timing is cowardly!
